rComments: I think he is the best professor for teaching this course. He is extremely eloquent and knowledgeable. It will be one of the best classes you ever had at UTSC.
He's a cool guy, shout out to you Andy, keep up the good work

Outstanding professor. Dr. Lee is extremely eloquent, organized, and thoughtful. He designed the course intelligently. Assignments and tests were extremely fair, relevant, and meaningful. He delivers his lectures phenomenally. It was an EXTREMELY fruitful and enriching learning experience. I will miss this course!
Brilliant professor. So well-organized and so great at explaining things.

Prof. Lee's lectures are really clear! They do overlap with the textbook and he'll only test you on things in lecture, so just take detailed lec notes and fall back on the text if need be (you can do well without it). Exams are hard and test if you know the content inside + out as they have 75-80 MCQ's for 4 lectures worth of content.

He discusses the theories and current topics within the areas of memory and perception very well. He encourages you to think and critically dissect theories and experiments that have been published which strongly adds to your understanding of the material. For those interested in cognitive psychologyneuroscience taking this course is recommended
Tough...but very fair. A lot of studies he expects you to know + dense readings.

Really nitpicky with his exam questions. All from lecture, but tests your memory. Class had trouble with his sample questions he asked in class. Don't understand why this course isn't offered to Neurosci majors but only Psych when I've done more Neuro in this class than I have in my C-Level neuro classes!!
